        PRG
      </h2>
      <p>
        The Post-Redirect-Get (PRG) is a design pattern useful in preventing the user from accidentally resubmitting the same form data by clicking the back button or refreshing the page, which could result in duplicate form submissions and unwanted side effects. By redirecting the user to a new URL after processing the form data, the server ensures that a GET request is sent instead of a POST request when the user navigates back to the previous page.
      </p>
    </div>
