        Rate Limit
      </h2>
      <p>
        Rate limiting is a technique used to control the rate at which requests or events are processed or delivered in a system, in order to prevent overload, improve reliability, and ensure fair resource allocation. It involves setting limits on the number of requests or events that can be processed within a given time period, and rejecting any requests or events that exceed that limit.
      </p>
    </div>
